+## Privacy Level
+
+hilal-privacy-header = Privacy Level
+hilal-privacy-description = Hilal privacy levels are explicit hardening profiles. They do not hide your public IP address, do not replace Tor Browser, and may break sites that depend on fingerprinting surfaces, WebGL, WebRTC, persistent cookies, saved passwords, or JavaScript.
+hilal-privacy-standard =
+    .label = Balanced (LibreWolf-like): strict tracking protection, RFP, HTTPS-only, URL cleanup, WebGL off, reduced WebRTC exposure, cookies/cache cleared on close.
+hilal-privacy-strict =
+    .label = Strict: Balanced plus First Party Isolation and WebRTC disabled. Safer for privacy, more likely to break video calls and sign-in flows.
+hilal-privacy-extreme =
+    .label = Maximum local hardening (not Tor): Strict plus JavaScript off, camera/microphone/location blocked, and browsing history cleared on close.
